{
  "video_id": "-83vVeSC2_g",
  "title": "Functionalism | Society and Culture | MCAT | Khan Academy",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 1910.0,
      "end_time": 3910.0,
      "text": "Functionalism is a\nsystem of thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3910.0,
      "end_time": 6610.0,
      "text": "based on the ideas of\nEmile Durkheim that"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6610.0,
      "end_time": 9610.0,
      "text": "looks at society from a\nlarge scale perspective."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9610.0,
      "end_time": 11370.0,
      "text": "It examines the\nnecessary structures"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 11370.0,
      "end_time": 13970.0,
      "text": "that make up a society\nand how each part"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 13970.0,
      "end_time": 16329.0,
      "text": "helps to keep the\nsociety stable."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16329.0,
      "end_time": 18470.0,
      "text": "According to\nfunctionalism, society"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 18470.0,
      "end_time": 20730.0,
      "text": "is heading toward\nan equilibrium."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20730.0,
      "end_time": 22910.0,
      "text": "I know it sounds a bit\nstrange that a society can"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 22910.0,
      "end_time": 26290.0,
      "text": "be at equilibrium, but consider\nthe changes many businesses"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 26290.0,
      "end_time": 29690.0,
      "text": "have had to make in response\nto companies like Amazon."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 29690.0,
      "end_time": 32100.0,
      "text": "Local businesses must\nadapt to find a new way"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 32100.0,
      "end_time": 36240.0,
      "text": "to cater to customers in\norder to restore the balance."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36240.0,
      "end_time": 38390.0,
      "text": "In the theory of\nfunctionalism, society"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38390.0,
      "end_time": 40950.0,
      "text": "is made from a bunch of\nconnected structures."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 40950.0,
      "end_time": 43330.0,
      "text": "One structure is\ninstitutions, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 43330.0,
      "end_time": 46350.0,
      "text": "are structures that meet\nthe needs of the society,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 46350.0,
      "end_time": 49190.0,
      "text": "like education systems,\nfinancial institutions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 49190.0,
      "end_time": 52530.0,
      "text": "businesses and marriage,\nlaws, mass media,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52530.0,
      "end_time": 54980.0,
      "text": "nongovernmental organizations,\nmedicine, religion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 54980.0,
      "end_time": 58350.0,
      "text": "the military, police forces,\nand lots of others, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 58350.0,
      "end_time": 61850.0,
      "text": "Another structure is what\nDurkheim called social facts."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 61850.0,
      "end_time": 64750.0,
      "text": "Social facts are ways\nof thinking and acting"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 64750.0,
      "end_time": 67430.0,
      "text": "formed by the society that\nexisted before any one"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 67430.0,
      "end_time": 71730.0,
      "text": "individual and will still exist\nafter any individual is dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 71730.0,
      "end_time": 74270.0,
      "text": "They are unique objects\nthat cannot be influenced"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 74270.0,
      "end_time": 76100.0,
      "text": "by an individual."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 76100.0,
      "end_time": 79350.0,
      "text": "They have a coercive effect over\nthe individual that is usually"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 79350.0,
      "end_time": 82220.0,
      "text": "only noticed when we\nresist against them."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 82220.0,
      "end_time": 85410.0,
      "text": "So for example, one\nsocial fact is the law."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 85410.0,
      "end_time": 87540.0,
      "text": "It is always there,\nbut we don't notice it"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 87540.0,
      "end_time": 90140.0,
      "text": "until we try and break\nit or act against it."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 90140.0,
      "end_time": 93610.0,
      "text": "Some other examples are moral\nregulations, religious faiths,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 93610.0,
      "end_time": 96890.0,
      "text": "and social currents like\nsuicide or birth rate."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 96890.0,
      "end_time": 99660.0,
      "text": "You might wonder how suicide\ncan be a social fact."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 99660.0,
      "end_time": 102570.0,
      "text": "Well, one person committing\nsuicide has no effect"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 102570.0,
      "end_time": 105140.0,
      "text": "on the presence of\nsuicide in the society ."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 105140.0,
      "end_time": 108180.0,
      "text": "Social facts are a facet\nof the society itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 108180.0,
      "end_time": 112450.0,
      "text": "and, according to Durkheim,\nare a necessary structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 112450.0,
      "end_time": 115030.0,
      "text": "But society is more than\njust the sum of its parts."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 115030.0,
      "end_time": 117580.0,
      "text": "It is dependent on the\nstructures that create it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 117580.0,
      "end_time": 120540.0,
      "text": "just like a cell is dependent\non all the little parts that"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 120540.0,
      "end_time": 121860.0,
      "text": "make it up."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 121860.0,
      "end_time": 124910.0,
      "text": "Every part of the cell has\na specific vital function"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 124910.0,
      "end_time": 127160.0,
      "text": "that depends on other\nparts of the cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 127160.0,
      "end_time": 129389.0,
      "text": "Without everything\nworking together smoothly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 129389.00000000001,
      "end_time": 130930.00000000001,
      "text": "the cell would die."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 130930.0,
      "end_time": 132890.0,
      "text": "The same is true of a society."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 132890.0,
      "end_time": 134630.0,
      "text": "Every structure\nhas a function that"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 134630.0,
      "end_time": 137360.0,
      "text": "meets a need of the society,\nand all the structures"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 137360.0,
      "end_time": 140090.0,
      "text": "work together to maintain\nthe social equilibrium."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 140090.0,
      "end_time": 142280.0,
      "text": "So for example,\nyou have schools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 142280.0,
      "end_time": 145030.0,
      "text": "which educate students so\nthey can find good jobs"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 145030.0,
      "end_time": 147260.0,
      "text": "and support the community."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 147260.0,
      "end_time": 150160.0,
      "text": "And businesses provide\nspecialized services."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 150160.0,
      "end_time": 153140.0,
      "text": "And laws maintain social order."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 153140.0,
      "end_time": 156210.0,
      "text": "These recognized and intended\nconsequences of institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 156210.0,
      "end_time": 158550.0,
      "text": "are known as manifest functions."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 158550.0,
      "end_time": 162200.0,
      "text": "But sometimes the institutions\nhave unintended consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 162200.0,
      "end_time": 164220.0,
      "text": "Schools allow the\nstudents and professors"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 164220.0,
      "end_time": 167470.0,
      "text": "to make social connections,\nand they expose the students"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 167470.0,
      "end_time": 170530.0,
      "text": "to new activities\nthrough extracurriculars."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 170530.0,
      "end_time": 174090.0,
      "text": "Businesses connect\npeople across societies."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 174090.0,
      "end_time": 177020.0,
      "text": "These unrecognized and\nunintended consequences"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 177020.0,
      "end_time": 180500.0,
      "text": "are called latent functions\nand are often indirect effects"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 180500.0,
      "end_time": 182160.0,
      "text": "of the institution."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 182160.0,
      "end_time": 184230.0,
      "text": "Now, Durkheim's\nmain question was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 184230.0,
      "end_time": 186470.0,
      "text": "what holds a society together?"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 186470.0,
      "end_time": 188300.0,
      "text": "How can it remain\nrelatively stable"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 188300.0,
      "end_time": 191920.0,
      "text": "even as traditions disappear\nand customs change?"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 191920.0,
      "end_time": 194490.0,
      "text": "He thought that small\nsocieties were held together"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 194490.0,
      "end_time": 198580.0,
      "text": "by their similarities, and the\nindividual was self-sufficient."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 198580.0,
      "end_time": 200480.0,
      "text": "But that only works\nfor small societies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 200480.0,
      "end_time": 203400.0,
      "text": "and we all know societies\nchange and grow large."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 203400.0,
      "end_time": 205110.0,
      "text": "The small society\nwould eventually"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 205110.0,
      "end_time": 208100.0,
      "text": "evolve into a large society\nwhere the individual"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 208100.0,
      "end_time": 210610.0,
      "text": "was interdependent on others."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 210610.0,
      "end_time": 213740.0,
      "text": "But what causes the evolution\nof society to occur?"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 213740.0,
      "end_time": 216360.0,
      "text": "The most basic factor\nis population growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 216360.0,
      "end_time": 218350.0,
      "text": "within a limited space."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 218350.0,
      "end_time": 220560.0,
      "text": "Suddenly there isn't\nenough land for everyone"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 220560.0,
      "end_time": 223300.0,
      "text": "to own their own farm\nand feed themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 223300.0,
      "end_time": 225580.0,
      "text": "So just a few farmers\ngrow enough food"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 225580.0,
      "end_time": 227360.0,
      "text": "for the entire community."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 227360.0,
      "end_time": 229140.0,
      "text": "But now the farmers\ndon't have enough time"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 229140.0,
      "end_time": 231730.0,
      "text": "for other necessities like\nmaking clothes or teaching"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 231730.0,
      "end_time": 232930.0,
      "text": "their kids."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 232930.0,
      "end_time": 235160.0,
      "text": "The people who no\nlonger have to grow food"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 235160.0,
      "end_time": 238440.0,
      "text": "now take on different roles\nlike tailoring or education."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 238440.0,
      "end_time": 240380.0,
      "text": "And everyone becomes\ndependent on one"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 240380.0,
      "end_time": 243300.0,
      "text": "another for their\ncontinued well being."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 243300.0,
      "end_time": 245330.0,
      "text": "People have become\nspecialized, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 245330.0,
      "end_time": 247470.0,
      "text": "forces mutual interdependence."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 247470.0,
      "end_time": 249280.0,
      "text": "This interdependence\nhelps to ensure"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 249280.0,
      "end_time": 251510.0,
      "text": "that the community\nwon't fall apart."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 251510.0,
      "end_time": 253880.0,
      "text": "Now that people depend on\neach other for the production"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 253880.0,
      "end_time": 255890.0,
      "text": "of goods and services\nthere's a need"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 255890.0,
      "end_time": 259660.0,
      "text": "for a method of distribution and\na way to control and coordinate"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 259660.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261740.00000000003,
      "text": "that production\nand distribution."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 261740.0,
      "end_time": 265360.0,
      "text": "In functionalism, a change to\neither production, distribution"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 265360.0,
      "end_time": 268420.0,
      "text": "or coordination will force\nthe others to adapt in order"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 268420.0,
      "end_time": 270960.0,
      "text": "to maintain a stable\nstate society."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 270960.0,
      "end_time": 274010.0,
      "text": "Social change is annoying\nand upsets the equilibrium"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 274010.0,
      "end_time": 276470.0,
      "text": "and threatens the mutual\ninterdependence of the people"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 276470.0,
      "end_time": 278210.0,
      "text": "within that society."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 278210.0,
      "end_time": 280300.0,
      "text": "The institutions and\nstructures of the society"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 280300.0,
      "end_time": 283210.0,
      "text": "adapt only just enough to\ncompensate for a change"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 283210.0,
      "end_time": 286730.0,
      "text": "and maintain the stability\nof mutual interdependence."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 286730.0,
      "end_time": 287550.0,
      "text": "Phew."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 287550.0,
      "end_time": 289760.0,
      "text": "All right, that just\nabout covers it."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 289760.0,
      "end_time": 291330.0,
      "text": "While functionalism\nis a nice way"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 291330.0,
      "end_time": 294170.0,
      "text": "to look at society with its\nequilibrium of institutions"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 294170.0,
      "end_time": 296735.0,
      "text": "all filling the needs of\nthe society they create,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 296735.0,
      "end_time": 299160.0,
      "text": "there are some\nserious problems here."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 299160.0,
      "end_time": 302250.0,
      "text": "Functionalism focuses\ncompletely on the institution"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 302250.0,
      "end_time": 305300.0,
      "text": "with little regard for the\nimportance of the individual."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 305300.0,
      "end_time": 308890.0,
      "text": "The individual is acknowledged,\nbut nothing they do really"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 308890.0,
      "end_time": 311370.0,
      "text": "affects the\nstructures of society."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 311370.0,
      "end_time": 313210.0,
      "text": "Functionalism is\nalso largely unable"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 313210.0,
      "end_time": 315670.0,
      "text": "to explain social\nchange and conflict."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 315670.0,
      "end_time": 317920.0,
      "text": "We know it happens,\nbut functionalism"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 317920.0,
      "end_time": 321030.0,
      "text": "is so focused on maintaining\nthe equilibrium of the society"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 321030.0,
      "end_time": 323120.0,
      "text": "that little significant\nchange is modeled"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 323120.0,
      "end_time": 325260.0,
      "text": "and no conflict can occur."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 325260.0,
      "end_time": 327690.0,
      "text": "The structures of a society\nadapt only just enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 327690.0,
      "end_time": 329760.0,
      "text": "to find stability again."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 329760.0,
      "end_time": 332660.0,
      "text": "Right, so, while there's more\nto understanding a society"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 332660.0,
      "end_time": 335370.0,
      "text": "than just looking at the\nstable state of its parts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 335370.0,
      "end_time": 337260.0,
      "text": "functionalism is\nhelpful in understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 337260.0,
      "end_time": 339580.0,
      "text": "the workings of\nsociety by examining"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 339580.0,
      "end_time": 342360.0,
      "text": "the functions of its\nintegral structures."
    }
  ]
}